# Notes Sidebar Button Styling Fix

## Overview
Fix inconsistent icon colors and types for sidebar collapse/expand buttons across all 3 Notes layouts.

## Issues Identified
1. **Color mismatch**: Collapse buttons (when sidebar open) used bright colors, expand buttons (when collapsed) used dim gray
2. **Icon mismatch**: Expand buttons used `PanelLeft` (no arrow), should use `PanelLeftOpen` (arrow out) to match collapse button's `PanelLeftClose` (arrow in)

## Files Modified
- `src/components/notes/FileTreeLayout.tsx`
- `src/components/notes/ThreeColumnLayout.tsx`
- `src/components/notes/TabbedSidebarLayout.tsx`

## Changes
For each file:
1. Changed import from `PanelLeft` to `PanelLeftOpen`
2. Collapse button: Changed icon color from `text-text-light-tertiary dark:text-text-dark-tertiary` to `text-text-light-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary`
3. Expand button: Changed icon from `PanelLeft` to `PanelLeftOpen`, color from `text-text-light-secondary dark:text-text-dark-secondary` to `text-text-light-primary dark:text-text-dark-primary`

## Result
- Both collapse and expand buttons now use primary text color (black in light mode, white in dark mode)
- Collapse uses `PanelLeftClose` icon (arrow pointing in)
- Expand uses `PanelLeftOpen` icon (arrow pointing out)

